Ex-first lady Patience Jonathan has petitioned the Bayelsa State Police Command over the demolition of a part of her property, Aridolf Resort Wellness and Spa, located in Okaka area of the state capital, Yenegoa.  Chairman of the State Physical Planning and Development Board, Gideon Ekeowe, who is also a former secretary to the state government (SSG), led the demolition by state government officials.Mrs Jonathan asked the police to arrest Mr Ekeowe over what she called abuse of office, criminal demolition and abuse of court processes.It was learnt on Saturday that the demand for the arrest of Ekeowe was provoked by the destruction of the hotel’s fence without allowing the management of the hotel and the Police respond to the court order arising from the motion on notice instituted by the physical planning board, reports The Guardian.The board has reportedly carried out around 78 cases of demolition which are being contested in court.The newspaper could not reach Ekeowe for comments, however, it said officials close to him noted that the action of the physical planning officials was backed by the ruling of the physical Planning Tribunal Development tribunal headed by Justice Emmanuel Ogola (rtd).  source By Ikechukwu Nnochiri ABUJA – The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC, on Monday, accused the wife of former President Goodluck Jonathan, Patience, of lying before the Federal High Court in Abuja that her property was illegally demolished. Patience Jonathan EFCC, in a 14-paragraphed counter-affidavit that was deposed to by… In "News" ABUJA - Former First Lady, Dame Patience Jonathan, has alleged that the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) sent assassins after her. According to Punch reports, Mrs. Jonathan said she had survived two of such attempts but urged the House of Representatives to quickly intervene before the EFCC would succeed… In "Top Stories" The Bayelsa State Police Command has dragged 15 persons to the state High Court sitting in 